    "Soft Landscape Specification",
    "Soft Landscape Management and Maintenance Plan",
    "Sunlight and Daylight Report",
    "Thereafter the development shall be retained/maintained in accordance with these details for as long as the development remains in existence.",
    "REASON",
    "To ensure that the development complies with the objectives of Policies. [Specify]",
    "The materials to be used in the construction of the external surfaces of the development hereby permitted shall match those used in the existing building and shall thereafter be retained as such.",
    "REASON",
    "To safeguard the visual amenities of the area and to ensure that the proposed development does not have an adverse effect upon the appearance of the existing building in accordance with Policy DMHB 11 of the Hillingdon Local Plan Part 2 (2020).",
    "Notwithstanding the provisions of the Town and Country Planning (General Permitted Development)(England)Order 2015 (or any order revoking and re-enacting that Order with or without modification), no additional windows, doors or other openings shall be constructed in the walls or roof slopes of the development hereby approved.",
    "REASON",
    "To prevent overlooking to adjoining properties in accordance with policy DMHB 11 of the Hillingdon Local Plan Part 2 (2020).",
    "The rooflights facing  55 Long Lane and Kelvedon Court shall be glazed with permanently obscured glass to at least scale 4 on the Pilkington scale and be non-opening below a height of 1.8 metres taken from internal finished floor level for so long as the development remains in existence.",
    "REASON",
    "To prevent overlooking to adjoining properties in accordance with policies DMHB 11 and DMHD 1-2 of the Hillingdon Local Plan Part 2 (2020).",
    "The parking shall be laid out and allocated as shown on submitted plan reference 03B  and shall remain allocated and dedicated in such a manner for the life-time of the development.",
